03:03:08,375 --> 03:03:20,172
17373, petition by Robert L. Capucci, Jr., 71 Evans Street, Medford, to address the council concerning municipal aggregation.

2209
03:03:21,141 --> 03:03:22,742
Name and address for the record, please.

2210
03:03:23,142 --> 03:03:24,363
Thank you, Mr. President.

2211
03:03:24,503 --> 03:03:27,725
I'm Robert Capucci, Jr., 71 Evans Street in Medford.

2212
03:03:27,805 --> 03:03:29,927
I'll try to be brief at this late hour.

2213
03:03:30,988 --> 03:03:44,457
Last summer, it was proposed that the city move towards municipal aggregation based solely on it would save the electric rate payers in Medford some money.

2214
03:03:46,298 --> 03:03:47,018
It went away.

2215
03:03:47,459 --> 03:03:49,360
Somehow it came back last Tuesday.

2216
03:03:49,929 --> 03:03:57,552
in a committee of the whole meeting under a new auspice of protecting the environment, Go Green.

2217
03:03:58,333 --> 03:04:13,199
There was a wonderful presentation brought by the company, supposedly going to be hired by Alicia Hunt, the director of energy and environment here in Medford, the chairman of the Go Green Medford community.

2218
03:04:13,980 --> 03:04:16,521
Basically, for the citizens that are watching at home,

2219
03:04:17,228 --> 03:04:32,423
It's a program whereby if passed, if it ever comes to a vote in this council and it does get passed, you're automatically opted into the city buying your power for you, your electricity, with the provision that you can opt out.

2220
03:04:34,505 --> 03:04:38,549
Understandably, what the company said last week was you can opt out at any time.

2221
03:04:39,310 --> 03:04:43,954
There was also a 30 day opt out clause in there.

2222
03:04:44,454 --> 03:04:52,981
But Councillor Marks at the committee of the whole meeting brought up the state law which is after 180 days you cannot opt out.

2223
03:04:53,341 --> 03:05:02,028
And getting into these government contracts doing things on behalf of the people, when they tell you, you know, we'll let you opt out at any time.

2224
03:05:02,872 --> 03:05:04,434
But the state losses something out.

2225
03:05:04,834 --> 03:05:21,371
I'm a little bit skeptical of the whole process I if they if this is really such a good thing They should present it and market it to the people as an as an opt-in if they want to not Force everybody all at once to be a part of this system.

2226
03:05:21,471 --> 03:05:23,193
I mean, that's a slippery slope.

2227
03:05:23,233 --> 03:05:23,793
Where does it end?

2228
03:05:24,054 --> 03:05:26,396
Is the City Council gonna vote that?

2229
03:05:28,064 --> 03:05:31,785
another company buys all my clothes for me, all my groceries.

2230
03:05:32,045 --> 03:05:35,766
It's, it's, it's, it's dangerous precedent that was sent setting.

2231
03:05:36,326 --> 03:05:36,926
It really is.

2232
03:05:37,326 --> 03:05:40,127
But I want to be fair to the other side.

2233
03:05:40,787 --> 03:05:47,489
Uh, councilor Della Russo at the committee of the whole meeting was a very astute and bringing up, I would like opposition to this.

2234
03:05:47,949 --> 03:05:53,970
So I emailed everybody on this council, the citizens against municipal aggregation website.

2235
03:05:54,431 --> 03:05:56,171
I also included the mayor and,

2236
03:05:56,858 --> 03:05:59,679
Alicia hunt, the director of environment and engineer.

2237
03:06:00,179 --> 03:06:06,062
I'm also going to reach out to them if it ever does come to a vote so that the opposite side could be heard.

2238
03:06:06,722 --> 03:06:17,127
I just find it just comforting that the city would entertain a notion of doing something on behalf of every resident.

2239
03:06:18,454 --> 03:06:22,979
from reading the CAMA website, it doesn't always work.

2240
03:06:23,420 --> 03:06:35,153
And if you are locked into it and they say you can get out, but on that 181st day you do try to get out, for some reason you can't, and a lower rate comes, I mean, you can go to the two sources now.

2241
03:06:35,213 --> 03:06:37,215
It's at Eversource and National Grid.

2242
03:06:37,616 --> 03:06:38,657
And you can click on them now.

2243
03:06:39,375 --> 03:06:42,717
And under those, a ton of other options come up.

2244
03:06:43,017 --> 03:06:45,738
There are choices for citizens to make right now.

2245
03:06:45,798 --> 03:06:51,381
They can enter into a six-month program for, say, $6.99 a kilowatt hour, or another program for $12.99.

2246
03:06:51,681 --> 03:06:59,285
That choice, which is pretty much the fundamental building block of this nation, should never be taken away.

2247
03:06:59,485 --> 03:07:00,686
Thank you very much, Mr. President.

